PANDA STONEWALL LLC REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE
Panda Stonewall LLC ("Panda Stonewall") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from an electric generation facility located in Leesburg, Virginia ("Facility") that is interconnected to the transmission system operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth Panda Stonewall's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the Facility pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff.
Panda Stonewall's revenue requirement consists of the sum of the charges for the following: (1) a Fixed Capability Component and (2) a Heating Losses Component. Total compensation for any twelve-month period shall not be less than the total annual revenue requirement, as specified below, except to the extent a monthly revenue requirement payment is reduced in accordance with the Adjusted Revenue Requirement provision of this Reactive Service Tariff. This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
1. FIXED CAPABILITY COMPONENT
The annual revenue requirement for the Fixed Capability Component is $2,041,576.
2. HEATING LOSSES COMPONENT
The annual revenue requirement for the Heating Losses Component is $10,018.
3. TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT
The total annual revenue requirement is $2,041,576 + $10,018 = $2,051,594. The total monthly revenue requirement is $2,051,594 / 12 = $170,966.17
ADJUSTED REVENUE REQUIREMENT The total reactive service revenue to be paid to Panda Stonewall under this rate schedule shall be reduced if the effective date for the Reactive Service Tariff is not on the first day of a month. For each day that the Reactive Service Tariff is not effective after the first day of the month, PJM will reduce Panda Stonewall's total monthly revenue requirement payment for the relevant month by the product of (1) the number of days the Reactive Service Tariff was not effective and (2) monthly revenue requirement divided by the number of days in the month.
